                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;@MarkAmery the migration guide isn&apos;t the documented behavior of the operator. For that you want to look at the language operators section of the manual for that &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.php.net/language.operators.comparison&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noreferrer&quot;&gt;php.net/language.operators.comparison&lt;/a&gt; the actual behavior behind this relies on various comparison functions of the API, like when you&apos;re doing  strcmp for strings, where you can not guarantee the actual return value in every single case. Sure, it&apos;s almost always 1, 0, or -1, but for the cases where you can&apos;t guarantee it like in wrapping libc&apos;s strcmp, you offer up the same defined behavior as the underlying spec to be safe&lt;/span&gt;

